<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871228-0036 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:Service Resources Corp.</HL><DD> 12/28/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SRCTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   A group including Gamco Investors Inc. and Gabelli Group Inc., lowered its stake in Service Resources Corp. to 28.5% of the common shares outstanding.    In a Securities and Exchange Commission filing, the group said it sold 52,600 shares of Service Resources, New York, a manager of back-office clerical operations, between Dec. 1 and last Monday at $3.50 to $4.375 each.    The group purchased 3,800 Service Resources shares between Dec. 2 and Dec. 7 at $3.75 each. As a result of the transactions, the group now holds 539,800 Services Resources common shares.    The filing didn't give a reason for the purchase or sale of shares. In New York, a spokesman for Gabelli Group, which owns Gamco, said the stock sale was &quot;normal investment selling.&quot; Service Resources officials couldn't be reached for comment.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading Thursday, Service Resources closed at $3.625 a share, up 12.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>